                <div class="jonra" data-uuid="e42ac8444a994ad4a30bb76ad711f659">
                    <h2 data-uuid="e8c74e99b63f46d1ad8bb2139d6a7a25">The Rescue of John Doy</h2>
                    <p class="source" data-uuid="72d540db517b407aa2763e67d989f735">Dr. John Doy was an abolitionist who lived in Lawrence, Kansas. On January 25, 1859, he was captured while trying to lead escaped slaves to safety. A jury in Missouri sentenced him to five years in prison. The sentence outraged many citizens of Lawrence. A group of ten abolitionists decided to undertake a daring rescue operation. They succeeded in freeing Doy on July 23. Soon after, Doy and his rescuers posed for this photograph.</p>
                </div>
